        "subtitle": "Algerian Forest Fires Data from 2012",
        "description": "## Algerian Forst Fires Dataset\n\nData Set information\n\nThe dataset inclueds 244 instances that regroup a data of two regions of Algeria, namely Bejaia region location in the northeast of Algeria and the Sidi Bel-abbes region located in the northwest of Algeria.\n\n122 instances for each region\n\nThe period from June 2012 to September 2012. The dataset includes 11 attributes and 1 output attribute (class). The 244 instances have been classified into fire(138 cases) and not fire (106) classes.\n\nAttribute Information:\n- Date: (DD/MM/YYYY) Day, month, year weather data infomation\n- Temp; temperature noon in Celcius degree\n- RH: Relative Humidity in %\n- Ws: Wind Speed\n- Rain: total day in mm\n- Fine Fuel Moisture Code(FFMC): index from the FWI system\n- Duff Moisture Code (DMC) index from FWI system\n- Drought Code (DC) index from FWI system\n- Initial Spread Index (ISI) from the FWI system\n- Buildup Index (BUI) from the FWI system\n- Fire Weather Index (FWI) \n- Classes Fire, Not Fire\n\n=== About this file ===\n\nAbout this file\nThis file includes 244 instances that regroup a data of two regions of Algeria, namely the Bejaia region located in the northeast of Algeria and the Sidi Bel-abbes region located in the northwest of Algeria.\n\n\n=== Columns & descriptions ===\n\nday: day\nmonth: from July to August\nyear: year 2012\nTemperature: Temperature at noon in C\nRH: Relative humidity in %\nWs: Wind speed in Km/h\nRain: Amount of rainfall in mm\nFFMC: Fine Fuel Moisture Code - It tells us how dry the surface layer of forest or grassland fuels are, and therefore how easily they might ignite and spread fire\nDMC: Duff Moisture Code - It is a numeric rating of the average moisture content of loosely compacted organic layers of moderate depth.\nDC: Drought Code - It is a numeric rating of the average moisture content of deep, compact organic layers\nISI: Initial Spread Index - It  is a numeric rating of the expected rate of fire spread. It is based on wind speed and FFMC\nBUI: Buildup Index - It is a numeric rating of the total amount of fuel available for combustion. It is based on the DMC and the DC\nFWI: Fire Weather Index - It is a numeric rating of fire intensity. It is based on the ISI and the BUI, and is used as a general index of fire danger throughout the forested areas of Canada.\nClasses: Classes of Fire and Not Fire\n",
